-- China Stocks Fluctuate; Software Producers Gain, Commodity Companies Drop
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-23T02:45:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/china-stocks-fluctuate-software-producers-gain-commodity-companies-drop.html

          
          
             China’s stocks fluctuated. Software
stocks advanced on expectations the government will boost
development of the industry. Commodity producers dropped after
the government said it will remove export tax rebates on some
steel and metals products.  
 The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, was little changed at 2,588.1 as of
10:45 a.m. local time, erasing a 0.8 percent gain.  
